RELATIONS (emit one entry per meaningful pair):
- "wraps": A introduces before B and B resolves before A commits. The backbone
  wraps the subplots — hard dilemmas normally wrap soft ones.
- "serial": A fully resolves before B introduces. Serial subplots never interact.
- "concurrent": both active at once, interleaved, neither nesting the other.

Do not create cycles (if A wraps B, B cannot wrap or precede A). The story
ENDS at a branched hard dilemma's resolution: never chain anything serial
after every hard dilemma — a subplot that must outlast a hard resolution
should be wrapped by it (or concurrent), not serial after it.
